%20associating%20freely%20with%20the%20NRA%20and%20its%20affiliates%20and%20with%20millions%20of%20Americans%20and%20from%20speaking%20freely%20through%20the%20NRA%20or%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20NRA%20or%20its%20members%2C%26quot%3B%20Correll%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20%26quot%3Bexcluding%20him%20from%20the%20national%20arena%20in%20which%20the%20debate%20over%20gun%20policy%20and%20legislation%20occurs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20interfering%20with%20his%20ability%20to%20participate%20freely%20and%20fully%20in%20national%20and%20state%20elections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20from%20a%20July%20court%20filing%20by%20lawyers%20for%20New%20York%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James.%20It%20details%20her%20request%20that%20the%20former%20leader%20of%20the%20National%20Rifle%20Association%2C%20Wayne%20LaPierre%2C%20be%20barred%20from%20any%20financial%20role%20at%20the%20non-profit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6691719d8893442a51562ec2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20York%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James%20wants%20Wayne%20LaPierre%20barred%20from%20resuming%20any%20financial%20role%20at%20the%20NRA.%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225692a8e7-b82c-4004-bfc2-2e3737042aac%5C%22%3EA%20second%20NRA%20corruption%20trial%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20four%20years%20since%20James%20sued%20the%20NRA%20and%20four%20of%20its%20top%20executives%2C%20alleging%20they%20illegally%20diverted%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20from%20the%20group's%20coffers%2C%20used%20the%20money%20for%20lavish%20personal%20trips%20and%20other%20perks%2C%20then%20retaliated%20against%20eight%20whistleblowers%20who%20urged%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20two%20of%20the%20executives%20reached%20settlements%2C%20most%20recently%20the%20lobby's%20ex-CFO%2C%20Wilson%20%26quot%3BWoody%26quot%3B%20Phillips%2C%20who%20agreed%20in%20May%20to%20abide%20by%20a%20decadelong%20ban%20on%20managing%20money%20for%20any%20nonprofit%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20trial's%20jury%20found%20Phillips%20must%20repay%20the%20NRA%20%242%20million%20in%20damages%20for%20enabling%20LaPierre's%20lavish%20lifestyle%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjury-luxury-yachts-wayne-lapierre-used-on-vendors-dime-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyacht%20trips%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20private%20plane%20travel%20at%20donors'%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20also%20found%20the%20NRA%20violated%20state%20charities%20law%20by%20looking%20the%20other%20way%20as%20LaPierre%2C%2074%2C%20plundered%20the%20gun%20group%20out%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%2C%20enriching%20himself%2C%20his%20family%2C%20and%20favored%20cronies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaPierre%20was%20ordered%20to%20repay%20the%20NRA%20%244.35%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Monday's%20trial%2C%20lawyers%20for%20James%20are%20now%20set%20to%20ask%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Joel%20Cohen%20for%20additional%20non-monetary%20relief%2C%20as%20allowed%20under%20the%20laws%20regulating%20all%20non-profits%20based%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20what's%20scheduled%20to%20be%20a%20two-week%2C%20non-trial%2C%20the%20legal%20teams%20for%20the%20AG's%20remaining%20defendants%20%E2%80%94%20the%20NRA%2C%20LaPierre%2C%20and%20current%20NRA%20secretary%20John%20Frazer%20%E2%80%94%20will%20argue%20that%20internal%20reforms%20are%20working%20well%20and%20no%20further%20relief%20is%20neccessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20%26quot%3Bremarkable%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20James'%20lawyers%20countered%20in%20a%20filing%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20said%20the%20NRA's%20new%20program%20of%20reforms%20is%20%26quot%3Bstill%20in%20its%20infancy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvidence%20at%20the%20second%20trial%20will%20also%20show%20that%20the%20NRA%20is%20already%20trying%20to%20avoid%20James'%20oversight%2C%20including%20by%20%26quot%3Bpursuing%20a%20change%20of%20its%20status%20from%20a%20charitable%20to%20noncharitable%20corporation%20under%20New%20York%20Law%26quot%3B%20the%20AG's%20filing%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaPierre%20routinely%20flew%20on%20private%20jets%2C%20was%20driven%20around%20in%20black%20cars%2C%20and%20stayed%20at%20luxury%20hotels%26quot%3B%20for%20years%20in%20violation%20of%20NRA%20policy%2C%20the%20filing%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20the%20NRA%20now%20maintains%20it%20was%20victimized%20by%20LaPierre%2C%20the%20evidence%20will%20show%20that%20the%20NRA%20has%20never%20sanctioned%20LaPierre%2C%26quot%3B%20despite%20knowing%20about%20his%20misconduct%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20announcing%20LaPierre's%20resignation%2C%20the%20NRA%20praised%20LaPierre%20for%20his%20many%20contributions%20to%20the%20organization%20over%20the%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NRA%20has%20yet%20to%20clearly%20distance%20itself%20from%20LaPierre%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20after%20the%20first%20trial's%20verdict%2C%20the%20lobby%20has%20not%20tried%20to%20collect%20the%20%244.35%20million%20in%20damages%20LaPierre%20owes%2C%20nor%20the%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20attorney's%20fees%20it%20spent%20on%20his%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NRA%20also%20hasn't%20ruled%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20paying%20for%20LaPierre's%20continued%20legal%20fees%2C%20James'%20lawyers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20leaving%20these%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20LaPierre%20repayments%20on%20the%20table%2C%20NRA%20lawyers%20are%20arguing%20that%20they%20are%20hemorrhaging%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202018%2C%20the%20NRA%20has%20seen%20a%20more%20than%2025%25%20decrease%20in%20membership%20and%20a%2064%25%20decrease%20in%20revenue%20from%20membership%20dues%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20one%20of%20four%20expert%20witnesses%20the%20NRA%20intends%20to%20call%20to%20testify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22794%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20showing%20plummeting%20NRA%20dues%20and%20contributions%20submitted%20by%20expert%20defense%20witness%20Scott%20Nichols.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66919b478893442a51565a7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22295%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chart%20showing%20plummeting%20NRA%20dues%20and%20contributions%20submitted%20by%20expert%20defense%20witness%20Scott%20Nichols.%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDues%20and%20contributions%20totaled%20%24280%20million%20in%202018%3B%20they%20fell%20to%20%24114%20million%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20witness%2C%20fundraising%20expert%20Scott%20Nichols%2C%20who%20is%20arguing%20that%20the%20NRA%20would%20lose%20still%20more%20money%20if%20forced%20to%20pay%20for%20outside%20monitoring%20and%20auditing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20NRA%2C%20James%20is%20asking%20Cohen%20to%20appoint%20an%20independent%20monitor%20who%20would%20audit%20and%20oversee%20the%20association%20to%20ensure%20donor%20money%20is%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrazer's%20role%20at%20NRA%20should%20be%20restricted%20and%20monitored%2C%20James%20is%20also%20asking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Court%20should%20impose%20a%20lifetime%20bar%20on%20LaPierre%20from%20serving%20in%20a%20fiduciary%20role%20in%20the%20NRA%20or%20its%20affiliated%20entities%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20wrote%20in%20a%20pretrial%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20be%20no%20opening%20statements%20Monday.%20Instead%2C%20the%20state's%20case%20will%20begin%20with%20testimony%20by%20regulatory%20compliance%20expert%20Jonny%20Frank%20and%20by%20gun%20rights%20advocate%20Charles%20Cotton%2C%20who%20has%20served%20as%20the%20NRA's%20president%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGun-safety%20groups%20said%20Friday%20that%20they%20continue%20to%20support%20James'%20efforts%20to%20bar%20LaPierre%20from%20any%20future%20fiscal%20role%20at%20the%20NRA.%20A%20lawyer%20for%20LaPierre%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaPierre's%20tenure%20at%20the%20NRA%20significantly%20harmed%20public%20health%20and%20safety%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Douglas%20Letter%2C%20chief%20legal%20officer%20for%20Brady%20United%20Against%20Gun%20Violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHis%20legacy%20is%20marked%20by%20widespread%20suffering%20and%20loss%2C%20and%20he%20must%20be%20prohibited%20from%20returning%20to%20any%20position%20of%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20Letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20no%20surprise%20that%20LaPierre%20is%20pushing%20to%20remain%20relevant%20at%20the%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20agreed%20Nick%20Suplina%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20law%20and%20policy%20at%20Everytown%20for%20Gun%20Safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20NRA%20is%20facing%20a%20potential%20compliance%20monitor%20and%20having%20its%20longtime%20leaders%20barred%20from%20nonprofits%20is%20evidence%20of%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20corruption%20that%20existed%20in%20the%20organization%20for%20so%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-of-wayne-lapierre-2nd-nra-trial-fights-resume-role-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720821742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669185319caa6ed01e014f9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-of-wayne-lapierre-2nd-nra-trial-fights-resume-role-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20National%20Rifle%20Association's%20former%20%26quot%3Bking%26quot%3B%20is%20fighting%20NY%20AG%20Letitia%20James%2C%20who%20he%20s