%3ERobins%20Air%20Force%20Base%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20removed%20a%20crucial%20inspection%20procedure%20that%20could%20have%20identified%20a%20worn%20propeller%20blade%20before%20it%20caused%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fequipment%2Fkc-130j-hercules%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EKC-130%20Hercules%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20crash%20in%202017%20that%20killed%2016%20troops%2C%20federal%20prosecutors%20allege%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24797724-james-michael-fisher-indictment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enewly%20released%20court%20documents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Michael%20Fisher%2C%2067%2C%20the%20former%20lead%20engineer%20responsible%20for%20C-130%20propeller%20maintenance%20at%20the%20Georgia%20base%2C%20was%20arrested%20July%202%20by%20federal%20authorities%20as%20part%20of%20the%20investigation%20into%20the%20crash%20in%20Mississippi.%20He%20faces%20two%20charges%20relating%20to%20false%20statements%20and%20two%20charges%20relating%20to%20obstruction%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFederal%20prosecutors%20alleged%20in%20an%20indictment%20that%20Fisher%20allowed%20technicians%20to%20stop%20conducting%20a%20key%20inspection%20procedure%20on%20propeller%20bores%2C%20causing%20a%20defective%20propeller%20blade%20to%20be%20placed%20back%20into%20service%20even%20though%20%26quot%3Bintergranular%20cracking%20was%20not%20detected%20and%20remediated%20at%20Robins.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BFisher%20was%20also%20one%20of%20the%20key%20decision-makers%20who%20removed%20the%20critical%20inspection%20procedure%20in%20August%202011%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20allege.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20C-130%20flies%20above%20an%20air%20force%20base%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669190f05439fb59cebd1bdc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20C-130%20flies%20above%20Robins%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20Georgia.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Jamal%20D.%20Sutter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFederal%20prosecutors%20say%20the%20propeller%20blade%20was%20placed%20back%20onto%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fmarine-corps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMarine%20Corps%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20KC-130%2C%20call%20sign%20%26quot%3BYanky%2072%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20carrying%2015%20Marines%20and%20one%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fnavy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENavy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20sailor%20when%20it%20suddenly%20crashed%20in%20a%20soybean%20field%20in%20Leflore%20County%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20on%20July%2010%2C%202017.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cause%20of%20the%20crash%20was%20determined%20to%20be%20a%20propeller%20blade%20that%20came%20loose.%20That%20%26quot%3Binitiated%20the%20catastrophic%20sequence%20of%20events%20resulting%20in%20the%20midair%20breakup%20of%20the%20aircraft%20and%20its%20uncontrollable%20descent%20and%20ultimate%20destruction%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Marine%20Corps%20crash%20investigation%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20revelation%20of%20Fisher's%20connection%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BYanky%2072%20incident%26quot%3B%20comes%20on%20the%207th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20July%2010%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crash%20investigation%20revealed%20%26quot%3Bgross%20negligence%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20maintenance%20culture%20at%20Robins%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20but%20%26quot%3BFisher%20and%20the%20System%20Program%20Office%20avoided%20scrutiny%2C%26quot%3B%20federal%20prosecutors%20said.%20A%20criminal%20investigation%20was%20opened%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20criminal%20investigation%2C%20%26quot%3Bfederal%20agents%20learned%20that%20the%20earlier%20Marine%20Corps%20investigators%20were%20misled%20about%20what%20maintenance%20procedures%20were%20in%20place%20in%20the%20late%20summer%20of%202011%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bin%20August%202011%2C%20engineers%20at%20Robins%20authorized%20the%20removal%20of%20a%20critical%20inspection%20procedure%20for%20detecting%20C-130%20propeller%20blade%20defects%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20indictment%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20C-130%20Hercules%20aircraft%20undergoes%20maintenance%20in%20a%20hangar%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6691912d9caa6ed01e015b6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20C-130%20Hercules%20aircraft%20undergoes%20scheduled%20maintenance%20in%20a%20hangar%20at%20Robins%20Air%20Force%20Base.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Joseph%20Mather%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20began%20zeroing%20in%20on%20Air%20Force%20Materiel%20Command%20Form%20202%2C%20a%20document%20that%20must%20be%20filed%20when%20maintenance%20personnel%20need%20to%20request%20permission%20to%20deviate%20from%20technical%20manuals%20when%20making%20repairs.%20Fisher%20had%20allegedly%20signed%20off%20on%20such%20a%20request%20to%20remove%20a%20certain%20inspection%20designed%20to%20examine%20propeller%20cracking%20in%20August%202011%20and%20denied%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFisher's%20statement%20that%20he%20would%20have%20never%20removed%20the%20penetrant%20inspections%20was%20false%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20indictment%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFederal%20agents%20later%20uncovered%20the%20Aug.%2019%2C%202011%2C%20email%20in%20which%20Fisher%20stated%20that%20he%20had%20'no%20problem'%20removing%20the%20penetrant%20inspections%20and%20also%20discovered%20the%20other%20Blanket%20Form%20202s%20in%202012%20and%202013%20in%20which%20Fisher%2C%20as%20the%20assigned%20engineer%2C%20had%20recommended%20removal%20of%20penetrant%20inspections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFisher%20is%20accused%20of%20making%20false%20statements%20to%20investigators%20and%20hiding%20information%20regarding%20those%20forms%20from%20officials%20looking%20into%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFisher%20attempted%20to%20obstruct%20the%20criminal%20investigation%20by%20intentionally%20withholding%20documents%20showing%20that%20he%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20removing%20the%20critical%20inspection%20procedure%20and%20providing%20false%20statements%20to%20federal%20agents%20in%20order%20to%20cover%20up%20his%20role%20in%20removing%20the%20critical%20inspection%20procedure%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20indictment%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20widow%20reacts%20to%20seeing%20her%20late%20husband's%20name%20on%20a%20monument%20honoring%20the%20victims%20of%20a%20C-130%20crash%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669192345439fb59cebd1ca3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJessica%20Jenson%2C%20the%20widow%20of%20Sgt.%20Chad%20E.%20Jenson%2C%20reacts%20to%20seeing%20her%20husband's%20name%20on%20a%20monument%20honoring%20the%2016%20troops%20who%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20KC-130%20crash.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%20photo%20by%20Lance%20Cpl.%20Samantha%20Schwoch%2Freleased%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFisher%20did%20not%20return%20a%20phone%20call%20and%20text%20messages%20Wednesday%20seeking%20comment%20on%20the%20latest%20information%20in%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20records%20do%20not%20say%20what%20the%20next%20step%20for%20the%20case%20will%20be%20or%20when%20Fisher%20is%20next%20expected%20in%20court.%20However%2C%20records%20from%20the%20time%20of%20his%20arrest%20in%20Florida%20note%20that%20the%2067-year-old%20is%20currently%20free%20on%20a%20%2410%2C000%20bond%20and%20had%20to%20surrender%20three%20US%20passports.%20Fisher%20was%20living%20